10/04/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Justice Ministry announced on Friday (April 8th) that it has formally requested that Serbia extradite Bozidar Vucurevic, the war time mayor of the Bosnian town of Trebinje, based on war crimes charges. Serbian police arrested him at a Bosnian-Serbian border crossing on April 4th. Vucurevic, who also helped found the Serbian Democratic Party, is wanted by Zagreb for war crimes against civilians committed during the shelling of Dubrovnik in 1991. (Tanjug, B92, Vecernje Novosti, Nazavisne Novine - 08/04/11)
